{
  "texts": [
    "The next trial would start after a delay varying randomly between 2 and 3 s after the beep.",
    "Participants were required to come back to the hand's initial position at the end of each action (grasp and place the glass, grasp and use the bottle).",
    "In both the social and personal trials, both the real and virtual confederate had to look up at the participants for a few seconds and then look down, in order to create a quick social contact and give the participant the impression they paid attention to the motor action performed.",
    "In the case 15% 0% Note: Participants gave their responses on a 7-points Lickert scale ranging from 1-\"Not at all [e.g., real]\" to 7-\"Completely [e.g., real]\".",
    "Percentages in bold indicate the modal value, namely the most frequently chosen response."
  ]
}